---
description: React / Next.js rules
globs:
  - "**/*.tsx"
  - "**/*.jsx"
  - "app/**/*.ts"
alwaysApply: false
---

## Next.js App Router
- Default to Server Components; add `'use client'` only when interaction is needed
- Fetch with async/await in components; avoid `useEffect` + `fetch` for data loading
- Use `loading.tsx` and `error.tsx` for route-level loading and errors
- Do not use `getServerSideProps` / `getStaticProps` (Pages Router)

## Components
- Order: imports → types → component → `export default`
- No `defaultProps`; use parameter defaults
- No `React.FC`; use `function Component()` directly
- Prefer UI primitives from the stack defined in `stack.md` over hand-rolled markup

## Hooks
- Custom hooks live in `hooks/use[Name].ts`
- Do not call `fetch` directly inside hooks; use the data layer from `stack.md`
- `useEffect` dependency arrays must be complete; do not silence lint warnings

## State
- Local state: `useState`
- Cross-component: follow the state solution in `stack.md`
- Server data: follow the data-fetching approach in `stack.md`; do not default to Redux
